# Node.js Smart Wallet & Gas Sponsorship Code Examples

Based on the documentation, here are the complete code examples for server-side smart wallet implementation:

## Installation
```sh
npm i @privy-io/node permissionless viem
```

## 1. Create Privy Wallet
```ts
import {PrivyClient} from '@privy-io/node';

const privy = new PrivyClient({
  appId: 'your privy app id',
  appSecret: 'your privy app secret'
});

const {
  id: walletId,
  address,
  chain_type: chainType
} = await privy.wallets().create({chain_type: 'ethereum'});
```

## 2. Create Viem Account
```tsx
import {createViemAccount} from '@privy-io/node/viem';

const serverWalletAccount = await createViemAccount(privy, {
  walletId,
  address
});
```

## 3. Create Smart Account
```tsx
import {toKernelSmartAccount} from 'permissionless/accounts';
import {entryPoint07Address} from 'viem/account-abstraction';

const kernelSmartAccount = await toKernelSmartAccount({
  client: publicClient,
  entryPoint: {
    address: entryPoint07Address,
    version: '0.7'
  },
  owner: serverWalletAccount
});
```

## 4 & 5. Create Client & Send Transactions
```tsx
import {createSmartAccountClient} from 'permissionless';
import {createPublicClient, http} from 'viem';

const publicClient = createPublicClient({
  chain: sepolia,
  transport: http()
});

const paymasterClient = createPimlicoClient({
  transport: http('your paymaster URL'),
  entryPoint: kernelSmartAccount.entryPoint
});

const smartAccountClient = createSmartAccountClient({
  account: kernelSmartAccount,
  chain: sepolia,
  paymaster: paymasterClient,
  bundlerTransport: http('your bundler URL'),
  userOperation: {
    estimateFeesPerGas: async () => (await paymasterClient.getUserOperationGasPrice()).fast
  }
});
```

The smart account client handles transaction requests with "gas fees sponsored" through the registered paymaster.

